              <decoNote n="Detail 7">Gold ruled section dividers</decoNote>
              <decoNote n="Detail 8">Gold ruled section dividers</decoNote>
            </decoDesc>
            <bindingDesc>
              <binding>
                <p>Cover made of a thin piece of brown leather covered with paper on the inside and attached to the top of the first membrane. Outside cover has gilt stamped frame and floral motif in the center; inside cover has gold frame and concentric circles around a crescent moon. Scroll is held on wooden bar with ivory wheels and is enclosed in a tightly fitted maroon case.</p>
              </binding>
            </bindingDesc>
          </physDesc>
          <history>
            <origin>
              <p>Calendar produced by an astronomer called Muṣṭafá, commonly known as Ḥikmetī-yi s̲ānī (rectangle with red background at end of scroll) in 1226 A.H. (1811) (between first two sections, under the headpiece).</p>
              <origDate>A.H. 1226 (1811)</origDate>
              <origPlace>Istanbul</origPlace>
            </origin>
            <provenance>Gift of Anne Baker Lewis in 1933.</provenance>
            <provenance>Formerly owned by John Frederick Lewis.</provenance>
          </history>
